    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This powerplant utilizes individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure VANOS variable valve timing system to deliver a linear 333 hp. Power is sent to the rear wheels through a 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and an M Variable Differential Lock. The chassis is well-sorted, with the critical subframe reinforcement already completed and a recent valve clearance adjustment documented. The suspension maintains its factory-tuned damping characteristics, providing exceptional turn-in and mid-corner stability. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the mechanical components are robust, including preventative rod bearing replacement. This is a technically sound driver's car for those who prioritize the analog feedback of BMW\u2019s most celebrated M-division era.",
